root: ^The familiar sea breeze soothes your worn out physique, ensuring you that home is near. The sound of buzzing conversations fill the air as you reach the shoreline.
^You trot along the stepping stones of the shore, leading you to the hive-shaped homestead.
^Your hivemates have been discussing your whereabouts, and are happy to finally see you. They bombard you with delight at your arrival.
^The bumbling beepeople gather around you and make sure you’re alright. They ask about the adventure you were on, even though it hasn’t even been a day...
^For some reason, you find yourself rather happy that the day turned out the way it did.
^A certain worrisome friend asks you, “Did you find enough nectar? Have you had something sweet to keep you going?”
